SIMPLE: personage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Personage
<hw>Per"son*age</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r"s⟦ucr⟧n*⟦asl⟧j: 48)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>personnage</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Form, appearance, or belongings of a person; the external
appearance, stature, figure, air, and the like, of a person.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧In <xex>personage</xex> stately.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hayward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The damsel well did view his <qex>personage</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Character assumed or represented.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
actors and <xex>personages</xex> of this fable.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Broome.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧Disguised in a false <xex>personage</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Addison.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A notable or distinguished person; a conspicuous or
peculiar character; <as>as, an illustrious <ex>personage</ex>; a comely
<ex>personage</ex> of stature tall.</as></def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Personal</ent>⟦br⟧
